I can be at a professional --
-This is about my momma,

12:17.940 --> 12:19.820
not your momma.

12:19.900 --> 12:21.030
-Hey.

12:21.110 --> 12:23.070
I need you guys
upstairs right now.

12:23.150 --> 12:25.070
[ Keyboard playing ]

12:25.160 --> 12:27.660
[ Thunder rumbling ]

12:27.740 --> 12:30.580
♪♪

12:30.660 --> 12:34.080
[ Applause ]

12:34.170 --> 12:35.620
-Run along, children!

12:35.710 --> 12:38.210
By the time you get out
of school tomorrow,

12:38.290 --> 12:41.380
these shelves
will be filled with treats!

12:41.460 --> 12:42.510
Bye-bye!

12:42.590 --> 12:44.840
♪ Whoa ♪

12:44.930 --> 12:46.390
♪ Yeah ♪

12:46.470 --> 12:49.640
♪ Stop by the candy
lady's house ♪

12:49.720 --> 12:52.220
♪ Best not tell your mother ♪

12:52.310 --> 12:55.020
♪ Every child's got
a favorite candy ♪

12:55.100 --> 12:57.650
♪ 'Cause no sweet tooth's
like another ♪

12:57.730 --> 12:58.940
♪ Oh ♪

12:59.020 --> 13:01.280
♪ Sweet tooth, sweet tooth ♪

13:01.360 --> 13:03.690
♪ Sweet, sweet, sweet tooth ♪

13:03.780 --> 13:04.820
♪ Alright, child, sw-- ♪

13:04.900 --> 13:07.450
-Momma!

13:07.530 --> 13:10.030
I got good news.
I have a date.

13:10.120 --> 13:11.740
-A date? Ha!

13:11.830 --> 13:14.750
You got to work
in the candy shop!

13:14.830 --> 13:17.370
And quick eating up
the merchandise.

13:17.460 --> 13:20.090
-You didn't never let me
have no candy as a child.

13:20.170 --> 13:23.210
But I'm an adult now, and
I'll eat all the candy I want.

13:23.300 --> 13:26.090
-Y'all shouldn't be talking
to each other like this.

13:26.180 --> 13:28.720
So much vitriol between y'all.

13:28.800 --> 13:30.760
You're mother and son, man.

13:30.850 --> 13:34.560
-Shut up, Kinesha!
-Uh, put the Mike & Ikes --

13:34.640 --> 13:37.810
I'm sorry -- on the --
in the dining room.

13:37.900 --> 13:39.190
You hold your tongue

13:39.270 --> 13:43.730
when you in my
living room/place of business.

13:47.740 --> 13:49.780
-He got a knife!
-He got a knife!

13:49.870 --> 13:50.990
-Oh.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.410
[ Keyboard playing ]

13:53.490 --> 13:58.500
♪♪

13:58.580 --> 14:02.590
-Son, I never seen that look
in your eye before!

14:02.670 --> 14:04.760
Go on with that knife!

14:04.840 --> 14:07.380
-Aah!

14:07.470 --> 14:09.590
-Action-packed.

14:09.680 --> 14:10.890
-Open up.

14:10.970 --> 14:13.930
It's me!
The police!

14:14.010 --> 14:16.140
-This ain't a play!
It's a crime scene!

14:16.230 --> 14:17.770
[ Laughter ]

14:17.850 --> 14:20.230
-Yeah, a crime scene where
everybody got their clothes on.

14:20.310 --> 14:21.480
That ain't real life.

14:21.560 --> 14:24.440
-Shut your naked ass up, sir!
-Hush!

14:24.530 --> 14:26.280
[ Thunder rumbling ]

14:26.360 --> 14:27.610
[ Keyboard keys clacking ]

14:27.700 --> 14:30.320
[ Computer alarm beeping ]

14:30.410 --> 14:35.040
-Well, I think we should
assume the worst.

14:35.120 --> 14:36.660
-I'm gonna lose all my records?

14:36.750 --> 14:39.250
-Not quite.

14:39.330 --> 14:43.960
My fear is that MNAX may
interpret the tornado as

14:44.040 --> 14:46.550
a first strike against the USA.

14:46.630 --> 14:47.760
[ Thunder crashes ]

14:47.840 --> 14:49.590
-♪ Deja ♪

14:49.680 --> 14:54.220
♪ Familiar like deja vu ♪

14:54.310 --> 14:58.310
♪ Red eye on a late night ♪

14:58.390 --> 15:01.850
♪ But I still remember you ♪

15:01.940 --> 15:03.310
♪ I've been falling down ♪

15:03.400 --> 15:04.900
-Ah, Ms. Odom,

15:04.980 --> 15:07.070
I've been looking
forward to this.

15:07.150 --> 15:08.820
Feels good.

15:08.900 --> 15:11.110
Ahh.
Ouch.

15:11.200 --> 15:12.660
Ouch! Ouch!

15:12.740 --> 15:15.990
Ouch! Ouch!
Hey! Ouch!

15:16.080 --> 15:18.160
-Simon! Wake up!

15:18.250 --> 15:19.580
You okay?

15:19.660 --> 15:21.080
-Hey, man.

15:21.170 --> 15:24.000
If I die, tell your mom

15:24.080 --> 15:26.500
she's wasting her talent
at the post office.

15:26.590 --> 15:28.300
-What?
-She thicc.

15:28.380 --> 15:30.300
[ Tornado siren wailing ]

15:30.380 --> 15:31.590
Too thicc to be...

15:31.680 --> 15:35.430
sitting behind a desk
with all that ass.

15:35.510 --> 15:37.430
-You got a concussion?
-Oof.

15:37.510 --> 15:40.390
-That tornado siren
is getting pretty loud.

15:40.480 --> 15:41.980
Good thing
they never hit Chicago.

15:42.060 --> 15:43.650
[ Thunder and lightning crash ]

15:43.730 --> 15:45.110
Damn!

15:45.190 --> 15:48.190
♪♪

15:48.280 --> 15:51.740
Help me! I'm wet!

15:51.820 --> 15:53.700
I'm wet and I'm fat
and I'm stuck!

15:53.780 --> 15:55.660
[ Thunder and lightning
crash loudly ]

15:55.740 --> 15:57.370
-Before I take you in,

15:57.450 --> 16:00.450
have you given your life
to Christ?

16:00.540 --> 16:02.960
-My momma's dead,

16:03.040 --> 16:06.290
and it's all my fault.

16:06.380 --> 16:07.880
-How do you know she died?

16:07.960 --> 16:09.800
Maybe it's you who died.

16:09.880 --> 16:12.720
-Wait a minute.

16:12.800 --> 16:15.180
What kind of police station
is this?

16:15.260 --> 16:17.050
-[ Laughs evilly ]

16:17.140 --> 16:20.390
Are we going to justice...

16:20.470 --> 16:23.810
or purgatory?

16:23.890 --> 16:28.230
Does my soul waffle
between death

16:28.320 --> 16:30.570
and this here life?

16:30.650 --> 16:31.900
-Waffles?

16:31.990 --> 16:33.700
Damn, I'm hungry now.

16:33.780 --> 16:35.990
[ Laughter ]

16:36.070 --> 16:38.870
-Oh, Momma,
I hope you can forgive me!

16:38.950 --> 16:41.500
-I hope we can forgive you
for this play.

16:41.580 --> 16:43.540
[ Laughter ]

16:43.620 --> 16:45.920
-Momma, it was all my fault.

16:46.000 --> 16:49.500
-Yes, it is, Momma.
It is his fault.

16:49.590 --> 16:51.260
-It's not funny!

16:51.340 --> 16:53.550
Stop with
the streetlights, huh?!

16:53.630 --> 16:55.180
They don't even get it!

16:55.260 --> 16:56.590
Did you even know
that was a streetlight?!

16:56.680 --> 16:58.550
-Hey!
This is a play?

16:58.640 --> 17:01.100
It feels more like a work.

17:01.180 --> 17:03.180
[ Laughter ]

17:06.850 --> 17:10.270
It's time to punch in!

17:10.360 --> 17:12.570
-I don't have a computer!

17:12.650 --> 17:15.030
This is off of a typewriter!

17:15.110 --> 17:17.990
You know how much ink
I used to write this play?!

17:21.370 --> 17:23.750
Anyway!

17:23.830 --> 17:26.500
That's the end of act one.

17:26.580 --> 17:27.750
-I thought that was
the end of the show --

17:27.830 --> 17:29.540
-Shut up!

17:29.630 --> 17:31.130
-Okay, let's take a vote.

17:31.210 --> 17:33.590
Who thinks this play
works as is?

17:33.670 --> 17:35.130
-Oh, my God!

17:35.220 --> 17:37.180
What are you doing?

17:37.260 --> 17:39.300
-Oh, so y'all don't think
this play works.

17:39.390 --> 17:43.020
Y'all don't think this is
brilliant writing right here.

17:43.100 --> 17:44.640
You know something?
Forget all y'all.

17:44.730 --> 17:46.230
You know what I'm gonna do?
I'm-a write a new play.

17:46.310 --> 17:48.690
A new play that's gonna
be called "It Did Work,

17:48.770 --> 17:50.310
But They Didn't Believe It,

17:50.400 --> 17:53.480
So You Had to Figure Out
Other People to Do Plays With."

17:53.570 --> 17:56.360
It's gonna be about y'all
and how you quit and --

17:56.450 --> 17:58.070
and you gonna be evil
because of that,

17:58.160 --> 18:00.410
'cause that's an evil thing
to do, is to quit on somebody.

18:00.490 --> 18:01.950
And you gonna be trying
to figure out

18:02.030 --> 18:03.870
are you going to purgatory
or are you going to hell.

18:03.950 --> 18:06.870
-That's the same story
as this play.

18:06.960 --> 18:10.000
-Man, screw you!
Hey. Okay.

18:10.080 --> 18:11.840
10 minutes, I need
you guys right back upstairs.

18:11.920 --> 18:14.630
-No, they hate the play.
-Oh, they can't stand it.

18:14.710 --> 18:16.630
[ Laughing ]
They really don't like you.

18:16.720 --> 18:18.260
You doing some good stuff
up there.

18:18.340 --> 18:19.840
But anyway, I need you guys
to come back upstairs,

18:19.930 --> 18:22.300
because guess what?
They're focusing their anger.

18:22.390 --> 18:23.850
You're giving them common cause.

18:23.930 --> 18:25.270
Unless, Officer, you'd like
to come upstairs

18:25.350 --> 18:26.850
and help me
do some crowd control?

18:26.930 --> 18:28.730
-Okay, no, so we have
to go upstairs and do this play.

18:28.810 --> 18:30.690
-Okay, no, we're not doing
the play, alright?

18:30.770 --> 18:33.020
They already talked me
out of it. They quit.

18:33.110 --> 18:35.360
Nobody wants to do it.
-Why not?

18:35.440 --> 18:36.990
-Because -- People don't even
get the story, man.

18:37.070 --> 18:38.700
-Of course they get the story.
What's not to get?

18:38.780 --> 18:40.030
The story is easy.

18:40.110 --> 18:42.530
It's about a guy who hates
the South Side.

18:42.620 --> 18:45.040
He thinks it's a shithole.
He can't stand it.

18:45.120 --> 18:46.660
He goes crazy into a rage.

18:46.750 --> 18:48.040
He kills the first person
he sees.

18:48.120 --> 18:49.210
Who can't relate to that?

18:49.290 --> 18:51.170
-That is not
what this is about.

18:51.250 --> 18:54.500
This beautiful, orchestrated
script right here is about

18:54.590 --> 18:59.260
a man who's been living with
one of his parents way too long,

18:59.340 --> 19:01.720
to the point they feel
like roommates,

19:01.800 --> 19:04.220
and they almost start
looking alike.

19:04.300 --> 19:07.390
And then one day, he kind
of loses it a little bit, right?

19:07.470 --> 19:09.890
And he's thinking
about killing that parent.

19:09.980 --> 19:11.480
But he doesn't.

19:11.560 --> 19:13.860
Because he's thinking about
all the times

19:13.940 --> 19:15.270
that parent nurtured him.

19:15.360 --> 19:17.730
-Uh, no.

19:17.820 --> 19:23.280
No, the story is about how your
elderly mother still had to work

19:23.370 --> 19:25.080
until the day she died

19:25.160 --> 19:27.910
and how that makes you feel
like a failure.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.580
I thought you knew that.

19:29.660 --> 19:32.790
-Ooh.
I can relate to that.

19:32.880 --> 19:35.090
You know, my daddy, uh...

19:35.170 --> 19:38.710
he still works the night shift
at the helicopter factory.

19:38.800 --> 19:43.430
I don't have the resources
to help him get out of that job.

19:43.510 --> 19:47.760
Every night, he's ducking
and dodging blades.

19:47.850 --> 19:50.270
They said I had NFL speed.
I don't have NFL speed.

19:50.350 --> 19:51.690
I'm slow.
-You are slow.

19:51.770 --> 19:53.270
-I am really slow.
-Yes.

19:53.350 --> 19:54.520
-So he's stuck.

19:54.610 --> 19:57.730
[ Clattering ]
Okay, 10 minutes.

19:57.820 --> 20:00.190
Hey!
Hey, put that down, okay?

20:00.280 --> 20:01.610
Get off of the chairs.

20:01.700 --> 20:03.660
-K! K!

20:03.740 --> 20:05.280
-What?
-I feel a weak spot.

20:05.370 --> 20:08.040
If I have something sharp,
I can break one of these flats!

20:08.120 --> 20:10.000
-Oh, wait.
I stole a crystal.

20:10.080 --> 20:12.120
-That's perfect!
-Let me try to reach it.

20:12.210 --> 20:14.330
-Okay.

20:14.420 --> 20:17.960
♪♪

20:18.050 --> 20:21.170
More arc!
-Sorry.

20:21.260 --> 20:23.300
Stole a few more.

20:23.380 --> 20:26.300
-Try to throw them up, not out.
More arc.

20:26.390 --> 20:28.930
-I think I got it.
One more!

20:29.010 --> 20:34.480
♪♪

20:34.560 --> 20:40.070
♪♪

20:40.150 --> 20:41.490
-Oh! Got it!

20:41.570 --> 20:44.860
-[ Distorted ] Yes!

20:44.950 --> 20:47.160
[ Thunder rumbling ]

20:49.080 --> 20:51.450
-Damn.
-Oh!

20:55.750 --> 20:58.000
[ Thunder and lightning
crash loudly ]

20:58.090 --> 20:59.000
[ People scream ]

20:59.090 --> 21:00.840
-Alright, look.

21:02.590 --> 21:06.010
I-I got something to say.

21:06.090 --> 21:09.680
I just want everybody to know
that if this is my last hour

21:09.760 --> 21:14.270
on the planet Earth,
I want you to know, I love you.

21:14.350 --> 21:18.610
I love every creature
in this universe!

21:18.690 --> 21:22.230
But I hate this
motherfucking play!

21:22.320 --> 21:23.990
I hate it!

21:24.070 --> 21:25.740
No more play!

21:25.820 --> 21:28.030
Come on!
No more play!

21:28.120 --> 21:29.570
No more play!
-Excuse me.

21:29.660 --> 21:32.200
Are they saying, "No more play"
or "No, more play"?

21:32.290 --> 21:35.540
-[ Chanting "No more play" ]

21:35.620 --> 21:37.290
[ Thunder and lightning
crash loudly ]

21:37.370 --> 21:38.710
[ People screaming ]

21:38.790 --> 21:41.420
Okay, uh, everybody --
everybody calm down.

21:41.500 --> 21:43.050
Those storm shutters
are keeping us safe.

21:43.130 --> 21:45.670
They are rated
for 100-mile-per-hour winds.

21:45.760 --> 21:47.380
-Yeah.
We're safe.

21:47.470 --> 21:50.390
-Tornados can get up to 300.
-Oh, no!

21:50.470 --> 21:52.560
-Okay, okay, okay.
Calm down.

21:52.640 --> 21:53.930
Technically --
Technically, that is true,

21:54.020 --> 21:55.560
but that's
some Florida bullshit.

21:55.640 --> 21:56.770
I apologize, young man.

21:56.850 --> 21:58.520
I forgot there were
children here.

21:58.600 --> 22:00.060
[ Banging ]

22:00.150 --> 22:02.400
Okay, honestly,
that could be anything.

22:02.480 --> 22:04.860
That could be a brick.
That could be a tree.

22:04.940 --> 22:08.200
That could be a-a loose bag
of garbage, like that guy,

22:08.280 --> 22:10.490
Tom Skilling, on Channel,
uh, WGN.

22:10.570 --> 22:11.410
He's terrible.

22:11.490 --> 22:14.080
-Let me in!
-Yeah.

22:14.160 --> 22:15.660
-We should --
We just need to ignore that.

22:15.750 --> 22:18.710
Just imagine that that banging
is, like, a drum solo.

22:18.790 --> 22:22.420
Like a crazy --
Sir, can I borrow this?

22:22.500 --> 22:23.800
Listen, listen,
it's like a drum solo.

22:23.880 --> 22:25.010
Our people invented the drums.

22:25.090 --> 22:26.720
Black excellence.
Black excellence.

22:26.800 --> 22:27.970
See?

22:28.050 --> 22:29.550
Let me in.

22:29.630 --> 22:32.430
Let me in now.
I wanna be safe.

22:32.510 --> 22:33.640
Ey, ey, ey, ey.

22:33.720 --> 22:35.060
Our people are so creative.

22:35.140 --> 22:36.680
Like, we always manage
to get through, like,

22:36.770 --> 22:37.930
the hardest of times.

22:38.020 --> 22:41.400
All we need is each other,
am I right?

22:41.480 --> 22:42.860
Just depend on ourselves.

22:42.940 --> 22:45.780
So, Spike, I love you to death,
but I disagree.

22:45.860 --> 22:47.610
I think we need
to finish this play.

22:47.690 --> 22:49.450
-Yeah!
-Thank you. Thank you.

22:49.530 --> 22:50.820
Just remember that come
next election.

22:50.910 --> 22:55.240
And we are gonna resume
the action in...

22:55.330 --> 22:57.790
-Exterior, jail.
-I'm on pins and needles.

22:57.870 --> 23:00.620
Let's finish watching it.

23:00.710 --> 23:05.340
-Y'all wrong for this!

23:14.680 --> 23:18.480
Y'all wrong for this!

23:20.230 --> 23:21.940
-Open up "D" block!

23:27.820 --> 23:29.150
You had everything --

23:29.240 --> 23:32.860
a good home, candy,
handsome cheeks.

23:32.950 --> 23:34.830
Why'd you do it?

23:34.910 --> 23:36.990
-You know how hard it is
to wake up in the morning

23:37.080 --> 23:39.580
and your bed is surrounded
by 12 kids wearing bonnets

23:39.660 --> 23:42.670
and durags talking about
how they want some goddamn candy

23:42.750 --> 23:44.380
from the candy store
that's not open yet?!

23:44.460 --> 23:46.460
-Of course I don't.

23:52.930 --> 23:54.260
[ Thunder rumbling ]

23:54.340 --> 23:55.550
-[ Sighs ]

23:55.640 --> 23:57.510
[ Wind whistling ]

23:57.600 --> 24:00.020
That woman was really hard
to live with.

24:06.940 --> 24:09.150
My momma never really made
anything of her life,

24:09.230 --> 24:10.990
to be honest with you.

24:13.070 --> 24:15.660
I used to blame myself for it.

24:15.740 --> 24:18.540
[ Scoffs ]

24:18.620 --> 24:21.620
I'm just realizing now
that it wasn't my fault.

24:21.710 --> 24:23.210
[ Keyboard playing ]

24:23.290 --> 24:26.880
♪♪

24:26.960 --> 24:31.050
♪ She dropped out
of high school twice ♪

24:31.130 --> 24:33.180
♪ It wasn't my fault ♪

24:33.260 --> 24:34.550
-Oh!
-Come on, Simon!

24:34.630 --> 24:36.300
You can do it!

24:36.390 --> 24:39.560
Come on!
Break free, man!

24:39.640 --> 24:43.230
-♪ She couldn't keep a job ♪

24:43.310 --> 24:44.640
♪ And she thought 9:00 a.m. ♪

24:44.730 --> 24:47.060
♪ Was too goddamn early
in the morning ♪

24:47.150 --> 24:49.070
♪♪

24:49.150 --> 24:51.690
♪ Boy, don't you talk to me
like that ♪

24:51.780 --> 24:55.160
♪ Marlene ain't gonna be
taking that mess from you ♪

24:55.240 --> 24:56.820
♪ Matter of fact, you didn't
learn to walk ♪

24:56.910 --> 24:59.870
♪ Until you was 4 ♪

24:59.950 --> 25:02.700
♪ You knew I had
a bladder problem ♪

25:02.790 --> 25:05.080
♪ But that don't mean
you had to pee the bed ♪

25:05.170 --> 25:07.790
♪ Well, Momma ♪

25:07.880 --> 25:11.300
♪ I still love you anyway ♪

25:11.380 --> 25:14.420
♪ But I'm-a tell you this now ♪

25:14.510 --> 25:16.680
♪ I don't need you ♪

25:16.760 --> 25:20.220
♪ I'm gonna step my game up ♪

25:20.310 --> 25:23.100
♪ I'm a man now, Momma ♪

25:23.180 --> 25:26.730
♪ I'm standing on my own
two feet, Momma ♪

25:26.810 --> 25:29.520
♪ Look at me now, Momma ♪

25:29.610 --> 25:31.980
♪ Look at me now, Momma ♪

25:32.070 --> 25:34.990
♪ Look at me now, Momma ♪

25:35.070 --> 25:37.280
[ Thunder crashes ]

25:37.360 --> 25:38.740
-Yes! You're free!

25:38.820 --> 25:40.450
-Ahh!

25:40.530 --> 25:44.200
-♪ I'm coming from
under that weight ♪

25:44.290 --> 25:49.540
♪ From under that weight ♪

25:53.210 --> 25:54.760
♪ Momma ♪

25:54.840 --> 25:59.930
♪ You raised a king ♪

26:00.010 --> 26:01.640
♪ Ooh-hoo, Momma ♪

26:01.720 --> 26:05.600
♪ Oh, you raised a king ♪

26:05.680 --> 26:07.060
♪ Ooh-hoo ♪

26:07.140 --> 26:08.480
♪ Momma ♪

26:08.560 --> 26:11.480
♪ You raised a king ♪

26:11.560 --> 26:12.860
♪ Ooh, yeah ♪

26:12.940 --> 26:17.320
♪ Momma, you raised a king ♪

26:17.400 --> 26:19.660
♪ Not a Dr. Luther King ♪

26:19.740 --> 26:21.320
♪ We talking
about regular king ♪

26:21.410 --> 26:22.660
♪ Me is a king ♪

26:22.740 --> 26:24.080
♪ We're talking about
Bishop the king ♪

26:24.160 --> 26:25.500
♪ I'm a king ♪

26:25.580 --> 26:26.870
♪ I'm a king ♪

26:26.960 --> 26:29.210
♪ I'm a king ♪

26:29.290 --> 26:33.500
♪ So, here's to li-- ♪
No.

26:33.590 --> 26:34.590
♪ Life ♪

26:34.670 --> 26:38.380
♪ To -- To -- To -- To life ♪

26:38.470 --> 26:39.430
♪ Life ♪

